abstract: Mr. Bennett, the author of “Before the Mayflower” and other books, was also a top editor at Ebony magazine for decades.
snippet: Mr. Bennett, the author of “Before the Mayflower” and other books, was also a top editor at Ebony magazine for decades.
lead_paragraph: Lerone Bennett Jr., a historian and journalist who wrote extensively on race relations and black history and was a top editor at Ebony magazine for decades, died on Wednesday in Chicago. He was 89.

abstract: In this week’s Canada Letter a reporter at the Olympics takes questions about the country’s performance so far and we highlight a new landmark on the prairies.
snippet: In this week’s Canada Letter a reporter at the Olympics takes questions about the country’s performance so far and we highlight a new landmark on the prairies.
lead_paragraph: Before Vancouver was host of the Winter Olympics in 2010, Canada created a privately funded program, Own The Podium, to avoid repeating the embarrassment of being a host nation that failed to win one gold medal, as was the case when the games were in Montreal and Calgary.

abstract: The search for the missing grain led to Trinidad and Thomas Jefferson, and now excitement among African-American chefs.
snippet: The search for the missing grain led to Trinidad and Thomas Jefferson, and now excitement among African-American chefs.
lead_paragraph: CHARLESTON, S.C. — Among the biologists, geneticists and historians who use food as a lens to study the African diaspora, rice is a particularly deep rabbit hole. So much remains unknown about how millions of enslaved Africans used it in their kitchens and how it got to those kitchens to begin with.

abstract: If the U.S.O.C. is really serious about the sexual abuse, then someone else needs to lead the organization.
snippet: If the U.S.O.C. is really serious about the sexual abuse, then someone else needs to lead the organization.
lead_paragraph: PYEONGCHANG, South Korea — Five days after Chicago lost the bid to host the 2016 Summer Olympics, finishing dead last in the voting, Stephanie Streeter stepped down from her role as the acting chief executive of the United States Olympic Committee. It showed that there was some accountability for an embarrassing failure and that someone needed to — and did — take the fall for a very public stumble.

abstract: Since taking up its Russia inquiry last year, the committee, once an oasis of country-first cooperation in a divided Congress, has descended into dysfunction.
snippet: Since taking up its Russia inquiry last year, the committee, once an oasis of country-first cooperation in a divided Congress, has descended into dysfunction.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Beneath the Capitol, in a secured room where the House Intelligence Committee is supposed to be pressing its inquiry into Russian interference in the 2016 presidential election, two dozen staff members await a construction crew.

abstract: How did a grouping of uncooked, sliced vegetables become the truest expression of a chef’s creative abilities?
snippet: How did a grouping of uncooked, sliced vegetables become the truest expression of a chef’s creative abilities?
lead_paragraph: FOR MOST OF human history, nobody ate a vegetable for pleasure. After all, vegetables have no evolutionary imperative to be delicious. Many fruits are sweet, to lure animals into snagging them and scattering their seeds, but vegetables play no role in reproduction — as roots, stems and leaves, they simply keep individual plants alive, without concern for the furtherance of the species. Our protohuman ancestors ate ferns and tubers as vehicles for nutrients and calories, nothing more.

abstract: Alec Baldwin was back as President Trump, while the former cast members Rachel Dratch and Tina Fey performed a sketch tracing the historical rivalry between New England and Philadelphia.
snippet: Alec Baldwin was back as President Trump, while the former cast members Rachel Dratch and Tina Fey performed a sketch tracing the historical rivalry between New England and Philadelphia.
lead_paragraph: Get attached to any New York institution and you will eventually see it replaced by something more contemporary, whether it’s the 7-Eleven that takes over the space of your favorite corner bodega or a new set of “Saturday Night Live” cast members who get handed the reins of its long-running parody of “Fox & Friends.”

abstract: This week’s Canada Letter explores Canada’s reckoning with sexual harassment and introduces another episode of On the Market in Toronto.
snippet: This week’s Canada Letter explores Canada’s reckoning with sexual harassment and introduces another episode of On the Market in Toronto.
lead_paragraph: After Jian Ghomeshi was fired as the host of a popular C.B.C. Radio program in 2014 and then arrested on five charges related to sexual assault, the hashtag #BeenRapedNeverReported quickly appeared on Twitter.
